articles.author: Andrew Jeong
articles.title: The year’s last supermoon will illuminate skies worldwide this week - The Washington Post
articles.description: The last supermoon of 2024, also known as the beaver moon, will peak at its biggest and brightest around 4:29 p.m. Eastern time Friday.
articles.content: The last supermoon of the year which is also a beaver moon will hit peak illumination Friday around 4:29 p.m. Eastern time. Divider This moon will coincide with other celestial events, including the Leonid meteor shower and the Pleiades star cluster. Divider A supermoon is defined as an astronomical phenomenon where a full moon looks larger and brighter than usual. It happens when the full moon occurs at the same time when it is closest to the Earth in its orbit. Divider The term “supermoon” was coined by astrologer Richard Nolle in 1979 to describe a full moon that occurs when the moon is “within 90 percent of its closest to Earth”. Divider At the opposite end of the moon sighting spectrum is the micromoon – when the full moon looks especially small and dull because it coincides with the point in the moon’s orbit when it is farthest from the Earth.

articles.author: Gabrielle Fonrouge
articles.title: Capri and Tapestry abandon plans to merge, citing regulatory hurdles - CNBC
articles.description: The parent companies behind Coach and Michael Kors saw their proposed merger blocked by the Federal Trade Commission.
articles.content: Capri and Tapestry called off their merger on Thursday after the Federal Trade Commission successfully sued to block the megadeal. Divider The two U.S.-based luxury houses “mutually agreed” that terminating the merger was in their best interests as they were unlikely to get regulatory approval before the deal was set to expire in February, according to a news release. Divider “With the termination of the merger agreement, we are now focusing on the future of Capri and our three iconic luxury houses,” Capri CEO John Idol said in a statement. “Looking ahead, I remain confident in Capri’s long-term growth potential for numerous reasons.” Divider The $8.5 billion acquisition, originally announced in August 2023, would have married America’s two largest luxury houses and put six fashion brands under one company: Tapestry’s Coach, Kate Spade and Stuart Weitzman with Capri’s Versace, Jimmy Choo and Michael Kors.

articles.title: Amazon launches Temu and Shein rival with 'crazy low' prices - BBC.com
articles.description: The price of products on Haul, which is being trialled in the US, will be capped at $20.
articles.content: Amazon has launched a new outlet called Haul which caps the price of products on sale at $20 (£15.79), in an effort to take on low-cost retailers Temu and Shein. Divider The online shopping giant unveiled Haul as a mobile-only experience available in its Shopping app for US customers on Wednesday. Divider It says shoppers can expect “crazy low prices” on Haul products that are “worth the wait” of up to two weeks for delivery. Divider Amazon’s Chinese e-commerce rivals have enjoyed rapid growth in recent years but also faced criticism over the environmental impact of making and shipping ever more cheap products. Divider “Temu and Shein have faced backlash both for taking advantage of import loopholes and for being wasteful and environmentally irresponsible,” Forrester retail analyst Sucharita Kodali told BBC News. Divider “This effort seems to have the same challenges,” she said of Amazon Haul.

articles.author: Allison Chinchar, Caitlin Danaher, Mia Alberti, Pau Mosquera
articles.title: Thousands evacuated as parts of Spain hit with nearly a month’s rainfall in one hour - CNN
articles.description: Severe thunderstorms and torrential rain have once again battered coastal Spain, causing flooding and evacuations just two weeks after the country experienced deadly flooding in Valencia and other nearby communities.
articles.content: Severe thunderstorms and torrential rain have again battered coastal Spain, causing thousands of people to be evacuated just two weeks after the country experienced deadly flooding in Valencia and and other nearby communities. Divider Over 4,000 people and a thousand homes have been evacuated in the Malaga area, according to a Thursday update from Antonio Sanz, the director of the Emergency Plan for the Risk of Flooding in Andalucia. Divider Five areas near the Guadalhorce riverbank were preemptively evacuated due to the risk of overflowing. Divider In just one hour, nearly a month’s worth of rainfall inundated the city of Malaga, in Spain’s Andalusia region, according to the country’s meteorological agency AEMet. The southern Spanish province picked up roughly 100 millimeters (4 inches) of rain so far on Wednesday, 78 millimeters (3 inches) of which fell within an hour. Malaga normally averages 100.5 millimeters in the month of November.
